Year 8 Mathematics – Practice Test
School Level: UK Year 8 (Grammar School)
Topics Covered:
	Prime Factorisation
	HCF (Highest Common Factor)
	LCM (Lowest Common Multiple)
	Laws of Indices
	Powers of 10
Time Allowed: 45 minutes
Calculator: Not allowed
Instructions:
	Show all working clearly.
	Write answers in simplest form.
	Use index notation where appropriate.
________________________________________
Section A: Prime Factorisation
1. Write 360 as a product of its prime factors in index form.
________________________________________
2. Find the prime factorisation of 540.
________________________________________
3. Express 252 as a product of its prime factors.
________________________________________
4. A number has prime factors
2^3×3^2×5

Write the value of the number.
________________________________________
Section B: Highest Common Factor (HCF)
5. Find the HCF of 84 and 126 using prime factorisation.
________________________________________
6. Find the HCF of 180 and 240.
________________________________________
7. Three numbers have the following prime factorisations:
	2^4×3^2
	2^3×3^3
	2^2×3^2
Find their HCF.
________________________________________
8. Two numbers have an HCF of 18.
One of the numbers is 90.
Write one possible value for the other number.
________________________________________
Section C: Lowest Common Multiple (LCM)
9. Find the LCM of 12 and 18 using prime factors.
________________________________________
10. Find the LCM of 24 and 36.
________________________________________
11. Find the LCM of 20, 30, and 40.
________________________________________
12. Two traffic lights flash every 24 seconds and 36 seconds.
After how many seconds will they flash together again?
________________________________________
Section D: HCF and LCM Combined
13. Two numbers have:
	HCF = 6
	LCM = 180
One number is 30.
Find the other number.
________________________________________
14. The prime factorisations of two numbers are:
	2^3×3×5
	2^2×3^2×7
Find their HCF and LCM.
________________________________________
Section E: Laws of Indices
15. Simplify:
2^4×2^3

________________________________________
16. Simplify:
5^7÷5^2

________________________________________
17. Simplify fully:
(3^2 )^4 ┤

________________________________________
18. Simplify:
4^3÷4

________________________________________
Section F: Powers of 10
19. Write 45,000,000 in standard form.
________________________________________
20. Calculate:
3×10^4×2×10^2

________________________________________
End of Test

